Inspections shall be made by the Commission or its designated agent during development to ensure
compliance with the certified plan and that control measures and facilities are properly performed
or installed and maintained. The Commission may require the permittee to verify through progress
reports that soil erosion and sediment control measures and facilities have been performed or
installed according to the certified plan and are being operated and maintained.
14.6.10 Flood Hazards. That the development of the site will minimize:
(1) Danger to human life and health;
(2) Expenditure of public money for flood control projects;
(3) The need for rescue and relief efforts associated with flooding;
(4) Prolonged business interruptions;
(5) Damage to public facilities and utilities.
